value.0: Aye, <lad/lass>? Something I can do for ye? Has ye business with the guild?
Take the road north, <lad/lass>. They say the gates be closed tight due to the sickness in Neverwinter, however... an' they'll not let ye in. Not to mention that they are waging a war.
The only temple in town is Tyr's, <lad/lass>.
Me name be Kendrack, head of the guild, here, and mayor of Port Llast. Also known as the First Captain. That enough for ye?
Zor be a minotaur, so he should stick out wherever he goes. He be strong and a fierce warrior... but is a wee bit simple in the head.
I am told that he is quite reclusive. Given his size, it be likely that he be hiding out in a cave somewhere.
The Stirge be a strange one. A gnome mage, it is said, who believes himself t' be the smartest man alive.
The gnome were sighted last in the wildlands along the South Road, though he could be anywhere there.
The Wyvern is an elven man, a renowned bandit who is familiar with the ways of the wood. He be deceptive and cunning, and skilled with the bow.
The elf has not been sighted, but I have little doubt he be hidden within the Neverwinter Wood. Best search for him there.
A female halfling who is known to be cruel and wicked. She be an assassin who comes out of Luskan.
I hear the city be closed up tight, however, so I doubt she'll be there. Last word I have of that one is that she was spotted east of town, and then all but vanished.
Yesgar be a fierce half-orc murderer, and it were he that masterminded the escape of all of these criminals.
Of all the ones that have escaped, 'tis Yesgar who has remained the most elusive. I have not a clue where he might be... though he will not stray far.
I wish ye luck, <FirstName>.
I'd be pleased to offer ye the bounty for it, then. Ye've certainly earned it
I'd be pleased to offer ye the bounty for it, then. Ye've certainly earned it

Nay, <lad/lass>. Ye've done more than enough for us, and I think ye deserve a final cut. As a proper send off, please take this large sum o' gold as a reward for single-handedly slaying all five of the bastards.

I've also told some of me mercenaries to continue working for ye. I'm sure the experience they gain be worthwhile. May their swords help you triumph against the evils of the Sword Coast. Best o' luck in yer adventures, my friend.

Of course! This town also be part of the Lords' Alliance, and Neverwinter herself has lent us aid time and time again. We have plenty of grain, fish, and produce to spare. I will dispatch a ship out at once. Mark my words, the denizens of Neverwinter shall not go hungry!
I'm looking for work, if you know of any.
Then I will go look for them.
I have Zor's ear.
I have the Stirge's ear.
I have Wyvern's ear.
I have Delilah's ear.
I have Yesgar's ear.
Did you have any additional work for me?
I was sent here to see if you can send some food supplies to Neverwinter. <StartAction>[Give him the letter.]</Start>
